  "body": "The current harness uses a small number of accounts and does not attempt to repost failed transactions.  Since ethereum does not allow non-consecutive noces this results in a “one goes out they all go out” problem.  \n\n* The test harness could be adjusted to use more accounts to lessen the effect of a lost transaction\n\n* The test harness could be re-written to re-post unsuccessful transactions.\n\nProbability: Occasional\n\nSeverity: Moderate\n\n",
